author: The Capital-Journal
title: Podcast: How will K-State football respond to season's first defeat?
text:
By The Capital-Journal 
MANHATTAN — There is no rest for the weary in the potent Big 12. Or the injured, for that matter. 
The Kansas State football team welcomes No. 2 TCU to Manhattan this Saturday less than a week after the Wildcats suffered their first defeat of the season — a crushing 36-34 loss on a last-second field goal by Oklahoma State. 
“(Oklahoma State) executed down the stretch and we didn’t,” K-State linebacker Will Davis said. “That’s part of our mantra for the week: To execute at crunch time.” 
How will the Wildcats (3-1) respond to their first defeat of the season? The Topeka Capital-Journal's Ken Corbitt and Tim Bisel analyze this on the latest edition of the KSU CatZone Podcast. Also discussed: Kody Cook's remarkable poise at quarterback, K-State's spotty performance on defense and why Zach Davidson might be the most Googled player on the K-State roster.
